#First things first. TOKEN CAPACITY.
#DO NOT OVERLOOK THIS ASPECT WHEN THINKING ABOUT USING AI PROMPTS FOR CERTAIN DEPARTMENTS.
#Tokens are basically the processing currency that LLMs, or in simple terms, AIs use to process your prompt in a conversation.
#"As a rough guide from OpenAI’s website, 100 tokens are roughly equivalent to 75 words..." the playbook states.
#You could use the enterprise version of a LLM but always look up the token cap on that specific version.
#Some may be weaker and others may be overkill for your work.
#For example why would you use a really powerfull AI that can easily handle 1 million words in a conversation for routine tasks?
#On another hand why would you use a really weak AI for extremly demanding tasks such as coding or project management?
#Rely on the Goldfish effect which is influenced by Tokens.
#The Goldfish effect makes the AI forget the beginning of the conversation fast even when using CO-STAR & JSON prompting.
#You do not want to build a CSS file for your site to get even with the GANTT chart your manager did and with which you've fallen behind with
#if your LLM doesn't remember what it generated earlier in the conversation.
#If you find yourself in a situation in which you have fallen behind with a task.
#DO NOT BY ANY MEANS TRY TO SOLVE IT WITH AN UNDERPOWERED LLM
#It will only make things worse.
